observations.recommendation:
We recommend that management:
Demand immediate liquidation of outstanding cash advances;
Prepare demand letters to be issued to concerned officers and employees for cash advances relating to travel purposes that remained unliquidated/unsettled for more than 30 days;
Strengthen the operation of preventive and monitoring controls on the grant of cash advances to ensure timely submission of its liquidation documents.

We recommend that the management require:

The Planning and Development Council to judiciously and meticulously plan projects/programs/activities (PPAs) to be included in the Local Development Plan and Annual Investment Plan indicating in details specific PPAs embodied therein and promptly implement PPAs embodied in the 20% LDF in order to optimize the delivery of basic services to the people;

The officers/personnel concerned to conduct in-depth analysis and ensure that Program of Works (POW) have been prepared in order to ascertain a more realistic estimates of work items and costs as basis in appropriating fund thereof.

